revision.text:
'''Nukisaki Shrine''' (貫前神社, ''Nukisaki jinja'', also called 一之宮貫前神社 ''Ichinomiya Nukisaki jinja'') is a [[Shinto]] shrine located in [[Tomioka, Gunma]] Prefecture, Japan. It enshrines [[Futsunushi]] no mikami (経津主命) and Himegami (姫大神) as its main [[kami]]. It holds its annual festival on March 15. It was the [[ichinomiya]] of former [[Kōzuke Province]]. According to legend, the shrine was founded by [[Emperor Ankan]] in about 534.
{{Commons category|Ichinomiya nukisaki-jinja}}
==See also==
*[[List of Shinto shrines in Japan]]

==External links==
*[http://www.nukisaki.or.jp Official website]

{{Shinto shrine}}
[[Category:Shinto shrines in Gunma Prefecture]]

